briefTitle: Study to Evaluate the Immune Response and Safety of GSK Biologicals' HPV Vaccine in Healthy Women Aged 18-35 Years
officialTitle: Phase 3, Open, Age-stratified Study to Assess Immunogenicity and Safety of GSK Biologicals' HPV-16/18 Vaccine Administered Intramuscularly According to 3-dose Schedule (0,1,6 Months) in Healthy Female Subjects Aged 15 - 55 Years and Long Term Follow-up
summary:
Human papillomavirus infection has clearly been recognized as the cause of cervical cancer. The infection of the cervix by certain oncogenic types of HPV, if not cleared, can lead to cervical cancer in women. This study will evaluate the immunogenicity and safety of the HPV-16/18 L1 VLP AS04 vaccine.

The Protocol Posting has been updated in order to comply with the FDA Amendment Act, Sep 2007.

primaryOutcome.measure: Number of Subjects Who Seroconverted for Anti-human Papilloma Virus 16 (Anti-HPV-16) and Anti-human Papilloma Virus 18 (Anti-HPV-18) Antibodies
